cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about extractive document summarization using Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs). The paper discusses two novel RNN-based architectures for this task and evaluates their performance on two different corpora. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, which makes cs.IR a likely sub-category as well. The paper uses machine learning techniques to build the models, which makes cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. Finally, since the paper uses RNNs, which are a type of neural network, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
